HEADWORD: Cuprous
<hw>Cu"prous</hw> <pr>(k?"pr?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cuprum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
derived from, copper; containing copper; -- said of those compounds of
copper in which this element is present in its highest
proportion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

